&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enigma is the most reliable, trusted source of data on businesses in the United States. Built on industry-leading entity resolution and the most comprehensive collection of trusted U.S. government data, Enigma powers KYB, screening and AML compliance, merchant payment risk, and go-to-market account-based data enrichment. Enigma provides ground-truth business identity and financial signal data that financial institutions, data platforms, and AI systems rely on to understand and verify businesses, delivered through APIs and Agents to support mission-critical workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re at an inflection point as a company: scaling both our product and the teams building it. Hiring exceptional people, particularly in engineering, data science, product, and GTM, is one of the most important levers we have.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Lead Recruiter who wants to operate as a true partner in building the company, not just filling reqs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a sourcing-heavy, end-to-end recruiting role focused on some of the hardest and most business-critical hiring problems at Enigma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll partner closely with technical and company leadership to identify, engage, and close high-caliber talent across engineering, data science, AI/ML, product, and go-to-market functions. Many of these searches require creativity, persistence, and strong judgment. The profiles we’re looking for are often highly specialized and rarely actively applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who enjoys going deep: understanding technical domains, shaping search strategy, influencing hiring decisions, and helping build recruiting systems that scale with the company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You won’t just run processes. You’ll help define how Enigma identifies and hires talent in highly competitive markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead full-cycle recruiting for high-impact roles across Engineering, Data Science, Product, and GTM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and execute creative, multi-channel sourcing strategies to engage top talent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop deep pipelines through outbound outreach, referrals, networking, and talent mapping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage candidates through the full interview process, including screening, scheduling and coordination, calibration, offer management, and closing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with hiring managers to align on profiles, calibrate candidates, and drive searches forward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously test and refine sourcing approaches, messaging, interview processes, and recruiting tools to improve conversion and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring insights from the market back to the team and inform hiring strategy, compensation expectations, and talent availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help elevate recruiting at Enigma by sharing best practices, improving processes, and contributing to a strong recruiting culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes This Role Exciting?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High Impact Recruiting Problems: &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll work on complex, high-signal searches across AI/ML, data infrastructure, product engineering, and GTM, often partnering directly with company leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;: This role spans the full recruiting lifecycle, from market mapping and outbound sourcing through closing and process design. You’ll have significant autonomy and influence over how recruiting operates at Enigma.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Embedded Partnership: &lt;/strong&gt;Recruiting at Enigma is highly collaborative and deeply connected to company strategy. You’ll work closely with hiring managers

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By way of introduction . . .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ve built out a best-in-class data asset and AI tools about businesses in the US. Our primary focus to date has been a sales-led motion targeting enterprise-size customers. We’re seeing indications that a much larger opportunity exists among non-enterprise businesses and agencies prospecting among small business. Our hypothesis is that we have the tech to offer a best-in-class product for this persona.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone to build out a successful business line in this market that contributes meaningfully to our ARR. Reporting to the CTO, you’ll investigate customer needs, figure out the product limitations that are critical to solve. You’ll position and market our product to capture this market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role with high-level of autonomy and accountability. You’ll get support and encouragement from the team, but many problems you’ll need to work through on your own. And you’ll be fully responsible for delivering a successful outcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Are Looking for Someone Who&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craves an entrepreneurial challenge, autonomy and total ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operates with a sense of urgency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to roll up their sleeves to make things happen and is comfortable writing and shipping code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wants to engage with and listen carefully to customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perseveres through difficulties and setbacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Goes where the evidence leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate is Somone Who&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is highly motivated by having impact and willing to push themselves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prefers to get something wrong and quickly course correct than delay a decision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Treats people kindly and loves winning as a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Enigma, we’re building the single, most reliable source of data on businesses to power the future of financial services. By engineering better data from hundreds of public and third-party sources, we aim to tell the complete story of every business, so that companies of every size can access the financial services they need to grow and thrive. Our core values – generosity, curiosity, ingenuity, &amp;amp; drive – guide everything we do, from how we make our most important product decisions to how we work with and support one another on a daily basis. We’re a team of curious, driven individuals with diverse backgrounds and skills, but we’re all passionate about engineering deeper understanding through data—together. If this resonates, we would love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Salary Range: $160,000-$210,000&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A note on salary ranges: we pride ourselves on paying competitively for our size and industry. Salary is one piece of a total Enigma compensation package that includes additional benefits and opportunities. All of our compensation packages include equity because we believe 100% of Enigma employees should have the option to purchase ownership in the company and benefit from the value we’re creating together.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time at Enigma. We’re on the cusp of releasing our next generation of small business intelligence products built on years of learnings in the space. We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Engineer to join our team and help shape the trajectory of these products. Your work will directly impact the accuracy, scalability, and predictive capabilities of our data platform, influencing key business decisions for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Data Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining our core small business data product. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to build out new product capabilities starting from raw source data, through scalable data pipelines and models to the customer interface. We embrace customer focus and end-to-end ownership so your impact will be measured by the value we deliver and the technical quality and maintainability of our product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the unmet needs of our customers and create capabilities to address these.&amp;nbsp; This usually involves a process of exploring data, prototyping, and evaluation, followed by the build of robust and maintainable data pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineer scalable and maintainable data systems that tell the story of millions of U.S. small businesses (we use Databricks SQL, PySpark, and MLFlow).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll be building on top of our innovative data infrastructure that’s designed for iteration and experimentation (uses Dagster for orchestration and LakeFS for data versioning).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply a data-focused, first-principles approach to problem solving. We value candidates who bias towards simple and elegant solutions but have the capability to implement state-of-the-art models and techniques when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire your teammates to perform at their best while fostering a collaborative, supportive team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes This Role Exciting?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ownership and Impact&lt;/strong&gt;: Work directly with customers and internal teams to build product capabilities in an environment of high-trust and responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Challenge&lt;/strong&gt;: Tackle complex data and engineering problems, balancing speed of innovation with scalability and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning&lt;/strong&gt;: Work on unique, high-impact data challenges that require creative problem-solving and cutting-edge techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have 5+ years of engineering or data science experience, including 3+ years working on distributed data systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has practical experience extracting value from data in a creative way to deliver customer impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cares deeply about creating value and wants to learn, ship, and iterate quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills and a desire to work in a cross-functional environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A principled, metrics-driven approach to solving complex data problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points If You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have built data products in the entity resolution, sales, marketing, KYB, or credit underwriting space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in Python, Spark and Databricks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
