&lt;p&gt;You’ll own key product capabilities end-to-end, shaping and implementing technical designs and roadmaps, using sound judgement and engineering principles, and iterating based on customer feedback and outcomes. This role is ideal for an engineer who enjoys working across the full product lifecycle, thrives in ambiguous problem spaces, and is motivated by delivering high-impact solutions that create real value for customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable, highly available, high-throughput, model-driven solutions and products, deployed in cloud and on-premises environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solve problems with containers, cloud infrastructure, and infrastructure as code (we use Docker, AWS, Google Cloud, and Terraform)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project milestones and schedules directly with client stakeholders and team members, identifying threats to timelines as they arise, escalating as necessary, and ultimately delivering on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pride yourself on writing highly readable, thoroughly tested code (we use Python and React)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience and passion for leveraging AI-assisted tooling like Claude Code and Cursor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is comfortable with LLM agent integrations such as MCP, API calls, and query optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies problems that others aren’t seeing and makes sure they get solved&lt;/li&gt;
